<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Addresses Importance of Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The education issue is, in the
final analysis, is quest for competent professionals and advanced
science and technology, and the crux of the matter hinges on the
work to build a strong China with high attainment of science and
technology and education, a top Chinese official today.
</P>
<P>
Li Lanqing, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
made the remarks in a panel discussion with members at the First
Session of the National Committee of the Ninth Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), which opened yesterday.
</P>
<P>
"We should not merely pay lip service to China's invigoration
by relying on science and education. Instead, we must take
action," Li said.
</P>
<P>
"This should be the consensus of the entire society, leading
government officials at various levels in particular," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li urged governments at various levels to provide more funding
in education and explore a mechanism to ensure an increase in
education input.
</P>
<P>
China should make rational use of the existing educational
resources by ways of cooperation, readjustment and combination so
that the resources can be turned into optimal use and the country
can attain the best benefit in teaching, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he called on the country to create still better
living and working conditions for teachers, especially the younger
ones at the institutions of higher learning, so that they can work
hard, live in contentment and shoulder greater responsibilities in
teaching and doing researches.  
</P>
</TEXT>
