<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Resettles 4.8 Million Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Some 4.8 million redundant Chinese
workers in the state-owned sector found new jobs during 1997,
according to a bulletin released today by the State Statistical
Bureau..
</P>
<P>
The bulletin indicates China had employed 696 million people
by the end of 1997, 7.5 million more than that of 1996. However,
the number of workers in urban areas stood at 147.6 million at the
end of 1997, down 850,000 on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The ranks of self-employed people in urban areas grew by
3.4 million to reach 26.7 million last year.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate in urban areas stood at 3.1 percent, up
0.1 percent on 1996. Official figures show nine million unemployed
people at the end of 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
