<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Urges Implementing Deng Xiaoping Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin called for
steadfastly implementing Deng Xiaoping Theory to ensure the
attainment of ambitious development goals mapped out at the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
After reviewing remarkable achievements the country has made in
recent years, Jiang said: "It is by no means a simple matter to
turn various goals set at the Party congress into realities.
Contradictions and problems confronting us are complicated. We
need to exert great efforts to study them and resolve them."
</P>
<P>
"As long as we persist in taking Deng Xiaoping Theory as our
guideline, adhere to the basic line and basic program for the
primary stage of socialism, strengthen unity among all ethnic
groups, all parties and people in all walks of life, correctly
handle the relationship among reform, development and stability,
and work hard with one heart and mind, we can certainly realize
our trans-century grand goals," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, made the remarks this afternoon when he
joined a panel discussion attended by members of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), which is in session here.
</P>
<P>
Jiang recalled that non-Communist parties and the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce have recently elected their
new leaderships.
</P>
<P>
He referred this as a major event in China's political life,
which he said helps consolidate and improve the patriotic united
front, multi-party cooperation and political consultation under
the leadership of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing close cooperation between the non-Communist parties
and the CPC, Jiang said that old leaders of the non-Communist
parties had devoted their wisdom and ability for the country's
revolution, construction and reform.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC is an important institution for multi-party
cooperation and political consultation under the leadership of the
CPC, and is a feature and advantage of China's political system,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that members of the Ninth CPPCC National
Committee would contribute more to safeguarding social and
political stability and promoting reform, the modernization drive
and the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, who presides over meetings of executive chairmen of
the presidium of the First Session of the Ninth CPPCC National
Committee, was present at the penal discussion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
