<HEADLINE> Mubarak Congratulates on Weizman's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
congratulated his Israeli counterpart Ezer Weizman on his
re-election for a second term on Wednesday, the Middle East News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak conveyed the congratulations during a telephone call to
Weizman after he was elected by the Israeli Knesset (parliament)
in the day.
</P>
<P>
Weizman won a clear majority of 63 votes in the 120-seat
Knesset and defeated his challenger Shaul Amor nominated by the
ruling Likud party.
</P>
<P>
He will assume the office of another five year on May 18.
</P>
<P>
Weizman has served as an air force commander and defense
minister and played a key role in negotiating a peace agreement
between Israel and Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
