<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Willing to Help Resolving Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Romania, worried over the recent
ethnic violence in Kosovo, said it is willing to help putting an
end to the crisis in the autonomous province of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anda Filip said Wednesday Romania,
as a neighbor of Yugoslavia, is deeply concerned over the situation
in Kosovo, where 90 percent of the population are ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
Romania likes to see the conflicting parties show restraint and
hold constructive and substantial dialogues to avert further
aggravation of the situation there, Filip said.
</P>
<P>
Romania supports the efforts by the international community --
the European Union and the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe in particular -- to bring peace back to
Kosovo, she said.
</P>
<P>
Tension in Kosovo heightened on March 1 after an escalation of
armed conflict between Serbian police and local ethnic Albanians,
during which four policemen and 16 Albanians were killed, and two
other policemen injured.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, who account for 90 percent of the population
of Kosovo, have been seeking independence from Yugoslavia since
1981. 
</P>
</TEXT>
