<HEADLINE> OAU Chairman Congratulates U.N. Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Organisation of
African Unity (OAU) and Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe Wednesday
sent a message to Secretary-General of the United Nations Kofi Annan,
congratulating him on the success of his mission to Iraq, reported
the Zimbabwe News Agency.
</P>
<P>
In his message on behalf of the OAU, the government and people
of Zimbabwe, Mugabe said the agreement reached with Iraq President
Saddam Hussein will contribute significantly to the peaceful
conclusion of the implementation of U.N.Security Council decisions
on the arms inspection in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
''The success of your mission has brought relief and joy to all
those who wish to ensure completion of UNISCOM's mandate and avoid
further military confrontation in the Middle East Region,'' said
Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe reassured Annan of his full support for this and other
untiring efforts in the quest for solutions to the many problems
confronting the world today. 
</P>
