<HEADLINE> China Eastern Orders Three Boeing Passenger Jets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Air Group has placed
an order for three Boeing 737-300 passenger jets, with a combined
value of more than 100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft will be delivered to the Shanxi branch of China
Eastern Air Group, based in Taiyuan, in July, October, and
November.
</P>
<P>
The order is part of the contract signed by China and the
United States during Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to the
United States last year.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 737-300 is a medium-range passenger jet, with a
cabin configuration of 138 seats, eight in first class and 130 in
economy. 
</P>
