<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Bankruptcies Hit Record Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Canadians posted the most
bankruptcies than ever before in 1997, reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Overall, bankruptcies rose to 97,497 in 1997, up nearly four
percent from the previous high of 93,860 set in 1996, according to
Industry Canada.
</P>
<P>
There was a record number of consumer bankruptcies, with 85,297
people filing for protection from creditors, which was seven
percent higher than the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
Business bankruptcies fell more than 14 percent to 12,200 from
14,229 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Canadian bankruptcies have increased dramatically since 1995,
rising nearly 24 percent despite robust economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The figures may reflect the growing proliferation of credit and
greater ease in obtaining it, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
