<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 16:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hamas Founder Leaves for Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Founder and spiritual leader of the
Palestinian Hamas organization Sheikh Ahmed Yassin left Cairo
Wednesday for Saudi Arabia to perform pilgrimage, the Middle East
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He will come back to Egypt before returning to Palestinian
self-rule area Gaza, an official at the Palestinian Embassy in
Cairo said.
</P>
<P>
Yassin, a 61-year-old quadriplegic with ear problems, arrived
in Egypt on February 19 for medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
He has received good treatment during a stay in a military
hospital, the Palestinian diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
Yassin's visit to Cairo was his first formal trip abroad after
being jailed by Israel for more than eight years for ordering the
killing of Palestinians who collaborated with Israel.
</P>
<P>
He was set free last October after a botched assassination by
two Israeli agents against a Hamas leader in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Yassin founded Hamas, or Islamic Resistance Movement, in 1987,
which insists that peace will not be realized until Israel returns
all the occupied Arab land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
