<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SAARC Tries to Accelerate Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC) will take a number of initiatives
this year to accelerate economic and trade activities among member
countries, said the grouping's Secretary-General Naeem U. Hasan.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua Tuesday at the Kathmandu-based
SAARC Secretariat, Hasan said the SAARC has a number of
initiatives this year for moving from the SAARC Preferential
Trading Arrangement (SAPTA) to a South Asian Free Trade Area
(SAFTA) preferably by 2001.
</P>
<P>
He said the commerce ministers of the seven SAARC member
countries -- Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal,
Pakistan and Sri Lanka -- will meet in Islamabad, Pakistan, in
April to make a full review of the achievements made in the past
two years in this regard.
</P>
<P>
And the third round of trade negotiations under the SAPTA will
be completed by the end of March, he said. This round of
negotiations had been scheduled to end in January, but was delayed
because the commerce ministers' meeting slated for February has
been rescheduled.
</P>
<P>
The previous two rounds have offered more than 2,000 items of
products for tariff cuts ranging from 10 percent to 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hasan said the list of products is expected to be expanded in
the third round and there will be a difference in focus.
</P>
<P>
"In the third round we're trying to deal with non-tariff
barriers. Before we were only looking at tariff barriers," he
said. "Secondly, instead of the (previous) commodity-by-commodity
approach, we're trying to adopt a sectoral (and across-the-board)
approach. This is one step forward," he said.
</P>
<P>
The most striking event this year will be the 10th SAARC summit
expected to take place in July or August in Colombo, Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the summit has not been finalized yet, but
traditionally economic and trade cooperation and poverty
alleviation are prominent, said Hasan, a career diplomat from
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Then an SAARC trade fair will be held in Sri Lanka, where
private investors, businessmen and traders will get together to
display their products, he said.
</P>
<P>
"To get trade and economic cooperation to succeed, you have to
involve the private sector," he explained. "Because today in all
the SAARC countries, the trend is toward deregulation and
liberalization, and our private sector has played a very important
role in complementing and supplementing the inter-governmental
process of economic and trade cooperation."
</P>
<P>
Besides, the non-governmental SAARC Chamber of Commerce and
Industry will meet this month in Islamabad and a conference on
economic cooperation is also scheduled for this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
"This year we intend to have a meeting on investment, because
we're trying to have a treaty on promotion and protection of
investment in the SAARC region," the secretary-general said.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC also intends to hammer out a treaty on avoiding
double taxation this year, Hasan added.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC, formed in 1985 to promote regional cooperation in
economic development and other areas, launched the SAPTA in
December 1995 as its first concrete measure for economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
At the ninth summit in 1997, SAARC leaders decided to bring
forward the timetable for the establishment of the SAFTA to 2001,
four years ahead of the previous schedule.
</P>
<P>
They had originally set the goal of realizing the SAFTA
hopefully by 2000, but not later than 2005.
</P>
<P>
"From the trend it is safe to conclude that the intra-trade (in
the region) is going up, but it is still unsatisfactory," he said.
</P>
<P>
Now intra-SAARC trade accounts for only 3 percent of the
region's total foreign trade. Hasan said the SAARC wants to
increase the percentage to 10-15 percent.
</P>
<P>
As to whether the SAARC can achieve the SAFTA by 2001, he said:
"That's the question nobody can answer. The work is going on, we
have to wait and see."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
