<HEADLINE> Uganda Population Program Gets Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Fund for
Population Activities (UNFPA) has donated 24 billion Uganda
Shillings to Uganda'population program, ''The New Vision''
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Virginia Ofusu Amaah, the Director for Africa Division of
UNFPA, said a few days before that the money will be used to
improve the quality of life of the ugandan people.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the UNFPA donated to Uganda 24 billion Uganda
Shillings.
</P>
<P>
According to the UNFPA official, infant mortality rate in
Uganda has dropped from 122 to 97 per 1,000 births during the
period from 1989 to 1995, maternal mortality has decreased from
700 to 506 per 10,000, while during the same period, the
fertility rate decreased from 7.3 percent to 6.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Population growth rate in Uganda has dropped from
3.8 percent in the sixties to 2.5 percent at the present due to
the efforts made by the government for population control.
</P>
</TEXT>
