<HEADLINE> Mobile Vocational Training Center to Be Set Up in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The first mobile vocational
training center will be set up in Angola this year with
assistance from Brazil, an Angolan government official announced
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Joaquim Oliveira Marques, Director of the National Bureau of
Vocational Education, said a news conference that the move aims
to further expand vocational education throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
He detailed that the mobile vocational training center after
completed in the second half of the year will provide mobile
teaching service in Angola's 18 provinces to enable more Angolan
people especially in remote areas to get educated.
</P>
<P>
The training center funded by the Brazilian government will
have a capacity of getting 2,000 people from all walks of life
trained every year, according to the director.
</P>
<P>
Marques noted that vocational education is an important part
of Angola's education sector and has contributed a lot in
improving people's education level and meeting the demands of
national building.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the National Bureau of Vocational Education which was
set up in 1992 has expanded vocational education to 15 provinces
from six provinces one year ago, he added. 
</P>
