<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Frenchmen See Economic Resumption in International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-nine percent of French people
think that the resumption of economic growth in France is the
result from the changes in the international economic context,
rather than that of the policy of any political party, said a poll
published Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by the BVA-BFM-Paris Match, was published
when the right opposition and left majority of France are
disputing who have contributed to the economic resumption and on
the eve of the regional elections.
</P>
<P>
Only 17 percent of the people polled said that the improvement
of economic situation in France is the result of the policy of the
Socialist government of Prime Minister Lionel Jospin, while seven
percent said it is due to the former conservative government of
Prime Minister Alain Juppe.
</P>
<P>
Conducted on February 27 and 28 among 952 people above 18 and
representing all walks of life in France, the poll shows that the
opinions of French people on economic growth converged beyond
partisanship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
