5.2 billion U.S. dollars worth of oil every six month, which aims
at alleviating the suffering of the Iraqi people who have been
living under the UN sanctions for more than seven year.
</P>
<P>
The new oil-for-food program will not be implemented until
Iraq submits its new distribution plan of humanitarian supplies to
the United Nations and gets the approval from the UN
Secretary-General. 
