<HEADLINE> France Happy with Surrender of Bosnian Serb War Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- France Wednesday expressed
satisfaction over the surrender of a Serb war crime suspect in the
French-controlled zone in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Dragoljub Kunarac, a Bosnian Serb accused of crimes against
humanity during the Bosnian War, Wednesday became the first war
crime suspect to be arrested by French troops serving in the
Stabilization Force (SFOR).
</P>
<P>
Kunarac, who was one of the eight Serbs accused of "killing,
beating and sexually mal-treating" many civilians in the region
of Foca, surrendered to the French in Filipovici, six kilometers
north of Foca in eastern Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
He is being transfered to the International Tribunal on war
crimes in Bosnia in the Hague.
</P>
<P>
The French Foreign Ministry said in a communique that the
arrest "makes up an important element in the implementation of
the peace agreements in former Yugoslavia," and that "France
considers all should be done to reach this goal." 
