<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ministers Backs UNEP Revitalization Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The High-Level Committee of
Ministers and Officials Wednesday agreed to back the efforts made
by the U.N. Environment Program (UNEP) to revitalize the
environmental organization.
</P>
<P>
In a statement adopted at the end of the two-day High-Level
committee meeting Wednesday, 36 ministers and officials elected
from among the U.N. members and its specialized agencies said
UNEP should be strengthened to ensure that it could serve as "the
leading global environmental authority".
</P>
<P>
The Committee welcomed the U.N. Secretary-General's decision
to establish a task force under the leadership of Klaus Topfer,
the UNEP executive director, to prepare proposals on reforming
and strengthening U.N. activities in the environment and human
settlement spheres.
</P>
<P>
"Strengthening UNEP and its voice in the field of the
environment is in our interest and that of the environment," said
Simon Moyo, an official attending the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In another communique on the funding of UNEP adopted at the
meeting, the committee said there was an urgent need to relate
work programs and budgets to realistic expectations for funds.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Topfer expressed the hope that member
states should set themselves the objective of improving the
funding of UNEP and of "bringing the level of funding for the
Environment Fund back to that of 1992".
</P>
<P>
The communique noted that the financial contributions by
member states to the Environment Fund had declined by one third
since 1992, which had prevented approved work programs from being
fully implemented.
</P>
<P>
It pointed out that the approved work program and budget for
the biennium 1998-1999 could not be implemented unless
contributions increased by 50 percent over current levels.
</P>
<P>
In another statement, the committee noted that freshwater
would be "an overriding issue of global significance."
</P>
<P>
The statement said sound environmental management and
development of freshwater resources as well as efforts to address
water quality issues were "a key to sustainable development,
especially in water-poor countries."
</P>
<P>
The committee agreed that UNEP should play a vital role in
providing substantial environmental input in freshwater issues,
in particular at regional and sub-regional levels.
</P>
<P>
The High-Level Committee of Ministers and Officials was
established under a decision at the 19th session of UNEP's
Governing Council held here last year as a consultation body.
</P>
<P>
It makes reform and policy recommendations to the UNEP
Governing Council and provides guidance and advice to UNEP
executive director. 
</P>
