<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Instructs to Combat Economic Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 4 (Xinhua) -- In order to timely prevent and cut
short economic crimes Russian President Boris Yeltsin Wednesday
signed a decree "On ensuring interaction of state bodies in
combating economic crimes", according to Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The decree says that the federal executive bodies, executive
bodies of subjects of the Russian Federation, as well as the
Central Bank of Russia, should inform the Russian Public
Prosecutor's Office without delay about crimes in the economic
area.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry and the State Tax Service should dispatch
specialists on demand of law enforcement bodies to participate in
checks and inspections on criminal cases of violations in the
economic area, the president decreed.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the prosecutor-general should inform the president
about measures taken to establish the most dangerous economic
crimes and administrative violations in the economic area, says
the presidential decree.
</P>
<P>
It was known that last year saw 210 thousands economic crimes
in the country, 7.5 percent increase compared with 1996. 
</P>
