<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
extended Tuesday's retreat and ended lower, dragged down by a weak
Dow, worries about possible interest rate rise and profit-taking
after recent strong gains.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE 100 index on the London market, Europe's biggest
one, closed down for the second consecutive session, depressed by
a weak New York, profit-taking in the heavy weight bank sector as
well as by concerns over a possible imminent rise in UK interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index tumbled back below the 5,800 level and
closed at 5733.1, down 74.6 points, or 1.28 percent.
</P>
<P>
