became jittery ahead of the Bank of England's verdict Thursday on
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The bank's two-day monetary policy meeting began on Wednesday,
with City analysts split on whether another rate increase is on
the way.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German's DAX-30 index fell from earlier record
highs and closed at 4,709.58, down 47.56 points or 1.00 percent as
the market was hit by profit-taking and losses in the debt market.
</P>
<P>
Shares prices in Paris retreated in line with other European
bourses and the strong dollar failed to help share prices as the
market began consolidating from recent all-time highs, with the
CAC-40 index closing at 3,381.32, down 33.55 points, or 0.98
percent.  
