<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus is ready to adopt a
national strategy for the creation of an Information Society,
Minister of Communications and Works Leontios Ierodiaconou said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ierodiaconou was addressing the Euro-Med Net '98 Conference on
Internet and the World Wide Web (WWW) which started here
Wednesday, with the participation of 300 representatives from
European and Mediterranean countries and European Union (EU)
officials.
</P>
<P>
Ierodiaconou said this strategy is expected to strengthen the
island's participation in the Global Information Society.
</P>
<P>
The basic ingredient for this national strategy is the
framework set by the EU itself for its member-states, a fact that
confirms Cyprus' full harmonization with the EU, in view of its
accession to it, the Minister noted.
</P>
<P>
The EU accession negotiations with Cyprus will begin on
March 31.
</P>
<P>
The Cypriot Minister also stressed that Cyprus can and wants
to actively contribute to turning the Mediterranean into an area
of peace and prosperity for all.
</P>
<P>
The four-day conference will deal with the subject of the role
of Internet and the World Wide Web in the development of the
Euro-Mediterranean society.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, there will be display of high speed
Internet connections via satellite and a host of European
companies will present the latest achievements in the field of
communication networks. 
