<HEADLINE> Germany's Unemployment Hovering at Record Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Germany's joblessness remained at a
post-war record high of over 4.8 million against a rate of 21.6
percent in February, official statistics showed today.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Labour Office in Nuremberg today put the February
joblessness at 4,819,400, down just 3,800 from the January level.
</P>
<P>
The data also showed that the gap between western and eastern
Germany continued to widen, with western German unemployment
dropping by 21,300 to 3,214,100 in February while the number of
jobless people in eastern Germany up 17,500 to 1,605,300 in the
month.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate in western Germany was 10.4 percent in
February compared with 21.3 percent in eastern Germany. 
</P>
