<HEADLINE> Bankruptcies in Germany Set New Record in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The number of bankruptcies in Germany
set a new record high with a total of 33,410 cases last year,
continuing the constant rise registered since 1992, the German
Federal Statistics Office announced today.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures included 27,485 company bankruptcies, up 7.7
percent from the 1996 level.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the Wiesbaden-based statistics office also noted that
last year's growth in bankruptcies was also the lowest in the past
five years, which seems to point to a stabilization of the
situation for the current year.
</P>
<P>
In an east-west breakdown, the office said western German
bankruptcies climbed five percent to 24,224 cases last year
compared with 19,359 cases in eastern Germany, up 6.9 percent.
</P>
