<HEADLINE> PLA General On Party Leadership, Army Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A People's Liberation Army (PLA)
general said here today that the Chinese army must subject itself
to the Party's absolute leadership, improve its quality and combat
strength with science and technology.
</P>
<P>
"We should firmly safeguard the authority of the Party Central
Committee and the Central Military Commission (CMC) with Jiang
Zemin at the core," said General Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of
the CMC, during a panel discussion of the PLA delegation to the
ongoing session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Zhang, a deputy to the Ninth NPC, is also a member of the
Political Bureau and the Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee,
</P>
<P>
"The history of the past 70 years proves that only under the
Party's absolute leadership can our army retain its character and
purpose, win one victory after another, and guarantee the
long-term stability and prosperity of our country," Zhang told his
fellow deputies.
</P>
<P>
He went on to note that under new historical circumstances, the
fundamental way for the Chinese army in accepting the Party's
absolute leadership is to keep ideological and political
consistency with and subject all its actions to the command of the
Party Central Committee and the CMC with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he urged the whole army to earnestly carry out the
decision by the 15th CPC National Congress and the ongoing NPC
session to further cut the PLA troops by 500,000, and spare no
effort to fulfil the goal in the next three years as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
"We shall also take this opportunity to implement the military
strategy and principles for the new period in a down-to-earth
manner, and persevere in strengthening the army through
the use of science and technology," he added.
</P>
<P>
Army building should be prioritized by setting up a scientific
military system and setup, stepping up the development of advanced
weapons and equipment, training and fostering a contingent of
highly-competent military personnel, and developing military
theories with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The general called for still greater efforts to fight against
corruption and promote socialist ethical and cultural progress in
the army.
</P>
<P>
Zhang also urged all PLA officers and men to increase their
political awareness and sense of mission by studying Deng Xiaoping
Theory, and provide a strong safety guarantee for China's reform,
opening-up and modernization drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
