<HEADLINE> Canada's Foreign Reserves Near Record Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Canada's foreign reserves hit 21.31
billion U.S. dollars in February, near its all-time high in March
1997, said a report released by the Finance Department.
</P>
<P>
A 2-billion-US-dollar bond issue and a halt in the four-month
tumble in the Canadian dollar allowed the Bank of Canada to
increase its foreign reserves in the month, the Financial Post
newspaper quoted the report as saying on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The country's foreign reserves increased by 3.31 billion U.S.
dollars to reach 21.31 billion in February, close to the record
high of 21.6 billion last March.
</P>
<P>
February was the first month since last September in which
Canada's central bank did not draw on its reserves to defend the
currency in the open market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
