<HEADLINE> Chinese PLA Urged to Build Fewer, Better Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A top Chinese general today
underlined the necessity of actively advancing the building and
reforming the People's Liberation Army (PLA), China's armed
forces, and embarking on the road towards fewer but better troops.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the statement in a
panel discussion attended by PLA deputies at the First Session of
the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), which opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also defense minister and vice-chairman of the Central
Military Commission, urged the army officers and soldiers to
earnestly implement the general requirements set forth by Jiang
Zemin, namely, to "be qualified politically, competent militarily,
sound in their style of work, well-disciplined, and assured of
adequate logistical support."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the top army officer noted, it is essential to
attach importance to combat-effectiveness of the armed forces, and
keep strengthening the army building by relying on science and
technology so as to push the modernization of the national defense
and the Chinese army to a new height.
</P>
<P>
After lauding the country's economic and social achievements
scored over the past five years, he expressed his full confidence
in the modernization of the Chinese army and the national defense
as a whole in the next century as well as in the future of
socialism and revitalization of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
"We must adhere to the Party's absolute leadership over the
army and rally still more closely around the Party Central
Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core," he said. "We must
be resolute in safeguarding the authority of the Party Central
Committee and the Central Military Commission, observe their
orders and be always at their beck and calls."
</P>
<P>
When asked about reducing the troops of the armed forces by
additional 500,00 persons within the next three years, he said
"this is a demand required by the situation and so it's an
important move for bettering troops".
</P>
<P>
The number of the Chinese troops was reduced by one million in
the 1980s at the order of late leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, "we should put the army's ideological and political
at the command, and bring out a new upsurge in the study of Deng
Xiaoping Theory," he acknowledgeed, calling for intensifying the
education among senior and middle-rank offices, further improving
the Party's work style, and retaining the character of the
people's army."
</P>
<P>
Chi also spoke of the importance of conducting nationwide
defense education and increasing the people's awareness of of
national defense in the panel discussion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
