<HEADLINE> Li Peng Calls for Greater Efforts at Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Environmental protection and
sustainable economic growth are two issues vital to the health of
the people and the interests of future generations, Premier Li
Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
"Environmental protection should be put on the agenda of key
matters of governments at all levels," Li said when he took part
in a group discussion attended by Beijing deputies to the National
People's Congress (NPC), which is in session here.
</P>
<P>
It is a good thing that more than 20 cities across the country
are making public air quality on a regular basis, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The air in Beijing is not good, but recently the municipal
government has decided to publish a weekly bulletin on local air
quality. This is a demonstration of courage and resolution," the
premier said.
</P>
<P>
Funds and technology are needed to improve the environment, and
these are what Beijing basically has, he said.
</P>
<P>
"With people developing a greater environmental awareness, the
environment in Beijing will surely improve," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Beijing, acting as the country's political and
cultural center and a center for international exchanges, should
meanwhile boost its economy.
</P>
<P>
With a large number of institutions of higher learning and
research institutes, Beijing enjoys great advantages in economic
development, particularly in the development of an information
industry, Li Peng said.
</P>
<P>
He urged municipal officials to show great care for laid-off
workers, noting that the problem can be solved with concerted
efforts from the state, enterprises, communities and individuals.
</P>
</TEXT>
