<HEADLINE> New Hotel Management Firm Formed in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A joint-venture hotel management
company, owned by Cheung Kong (Holdings) Ltd. and Hutchison
Whampoa Ltd., two heavyweights on the local bourse, has been
formed to undertake management and operation of hotels in Hong
Kong and beyond.
</P>
<P>
The new firm, Harbor Plaza Hotel Management (International)
Ltd., announced Thursday that apart from the 416-room Harbor Plaza
Hong Kong on the southern tip of Kowloon it currently manages, it
will take up the management of five additional hotels by the end
of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Three of the hotels are in the Chinese mainland while the other
two are in Hong Kong and the Bahamas respectively.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the current downturn in the Asian economy, we have
confidence in the long-term prospects of the global tourism
industry. The current economic downturn will also provide us with
good investment opportunities," said Dominic Lai, group managing
director of the company.
</P>
<P>
The company will operate under the trade name of Harbor Plaza
Hotels and Resorts. "The company's brand identity draws on the
international reputation of Harbor Plaza Hong Kong, which was
recently named one of the World's Ten Best Hotels by Leaders
Magazine of New York," Lai added. 
</P>
