<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Telecom Plans to Expand Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian
Telecommunications Corporation plans to double its capacity
to meet increasing demand for Internet service in the country, a
local report said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Berhe Seyoum, manager of external relations division of the
corporation, told local journalists that the corporation had
projected to connect only 1,000 users to the Internet, the
world's largest pool of information, within two and half years
since beginning operation in January 1997.
</P>
<P>
"Surprisingly, the demand for Internet service was so high
that within the first seven months, 1,300 subscribers have
already been registered," Berhe Seyoum was quoted by the as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said, at present Ethio-Internet has over 2,000 active users
in Addis Ababa and regional towns.
</P>
<P>
The corporation wants to upgrade its potential capacity from
the present 5,000 to 10,000 users, he said. 
</P>
