<HEADLINE> Zico Joins Brazil World Cup Coaching Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Brazil former World Cup
striker Zico has been appointed to the coaching group on Wednesday
to improve Brazil's recent poor form with three months to go
before the France Open.
</P>
<P>
Zico, who scored 66 goals for Brazil in 88 appearances, will be
number two to head coach Mario Zagallo as the technical
coordinator, according to the Brazilian Football Confederation
(CBF).
</P>
<P>
"I am not concerned about whether I will be above Zagallo or
under him," Zico said at CBF headquarters. "My only concern is to
help the Brazil team do its best for Brazilian soccer."
</P>
<P>
Zagallo has publicly stated he does not want an assistant.
But after Brazil's defeat by the United States in the CONCACAF
Gold Cup in February, when they also drew with lowly Jamaica and
Guatemala, the CBF came under intense pressure to make changes.
</P>
<P>
"The coaching staff is now in a stronger position for Brazil
to win the World Cup for a fifth time. God willing, we will,"
Zagallo told a news conference.
</P>
<P>
CBF president Ricardo Teixeira said Zico's role would be
similar to that played by Zagallo in the 1994 World Cup as
assistant to then coach Carlos Alberto Parreira. 
</P>
</TEXT>
