<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts East China Export Commodities Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The '98 East China Export
Commodities Trade Fair, which opened today in China's largest
trade and financial center Shanghai, has attracted over 2,000
exhibitors.
</P>
<P>
The fair, currently the largest regional event of its kind in
China, will have tens of thousand of name-brand and high-tech
exhibits, including that of light, textile, food and chemical
industries, according to Huang Jinyue, secretary-general of
organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
More than 50,000 businessmen from 130 countries and regions
have attended similar trade fairs held over the past few years,
with the total transaction volume for said events standing at 12.4
billion US dollars, according to Huang, who also serves as deputy
secretary of Shanghai municipal government.
</P>
<P>
East China, including Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Anhui, Fujian,
Jiangxi, and Shandong provinces, and major cities such as
Shanghai, Nanjing and Ningbo, covers approximately eight percent
of the nation's total territory.
</P>
<P>
The region's GDP has grown by an average annual rate of over 18
percent, or twice the national average, over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The region's total 1997 GDP hit 2.69 trillion yuan, with its
foreign trade volume of 107.8 billion US dollars accounting for
nearly 33 percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
The region has attracted foreign capital of over 24.6 billion
US dollars over the past few years, said Huang.  
</P>
</TEXT>
