<HEADLINE> Senior Lawmaker Encourages NPC Deputies to Speak People's Minds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, an executive chairman of the presidium of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC), which is currently in session
here, said NPC deputies should give expression to people's
feelings and accurately reflect their criticism of and suggestions
for the government.
</P>
<P>
"We should tell the truth, good or bad," said Tian, who is also
a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
"Only by doing so can we live up to the expectations of the
people," he said, adding there are 3.6 million deputies to
people's congresses of all levels across the country.
</P>
<P>
Tian said, "If all of us can tell the truth, people's
congresses will make immeasurable contributions to the country,
and only in this way can our country really have long-term
stability and prosperity."
</P>
<P>
Tian made the remarks when he took part in a group discussion
attended by deputies from Guangdong, an economically developed
province in south China.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong is the pioneer in the country's reform and opening
up. It has achieved the fastest economic growth and contributed
most to the country's economic development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tian expressed his hope that Guangdong would continue to
spearhead China's reform and opening up.  
</P>
