<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two-way Trade Between Vietnam, UK Up 68 Percent in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Two-way trade between Vietnam and
Britain was a record high in 1997 with a total of 501 million
U.S. dollars, Vietnam News Agency (VNA) said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a press release by the British embassy here
as saying that the two-way trade volume rose 68 percent compared
to that of 1996, when 344 million dollars were registered.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's exports to Britain was up 32 percent to 346 million
dollars, including manufactured goods such as shoes and garments
and farm produce like coffee, tea, spices and fish products.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, British exports to Vietnam, mainly manufactured
products and industrial goods, almost doubled that of 1996 to 156
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has had a surplus with Britain since the two-way trade
took off in 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
