<HEADLINE> Chinese Ethnic Area to Build New Agricultural Growth Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region in northwestern China is increasing efforts to develop
agriculture and build pillar industries and economic growth areas.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to the wine, meat, dairy,
pharmaceutical, grain processing, down and fur processing, and
vegetable and fruit processing industries, according to Ma Qizhi,
acting chairman of the regional government. It will increase
agricultural industrialization of these and turn its resources
into an economic advantage.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 percent of major agricultural products have begun to
benefit from the integration of trade, industry, and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The region harvested 2.56 million tons of grain in 1997 and
farmers averaged 1,540 yuan of income per capita, a 7 percent
increase in real terms. Over the next decade, it will increase its
330,000 ha of irrigated farmland to more than 660,000 ha.
</P>
<P>
The region is trying to build some leading agriculture-related
enterprises with more than 100 million yuan in annual sales, and
hold country fairs that do 100 million yuan in business annually,
Ma said. 
</P>
