<HEADLINE> King Hussein of Jordan Visits Oman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan arrived
Oman Thursday afternoon on a three-day visit after ending his tour
to the United Arab Emirates (UAE), the official Omani news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to hold talks with Oman's Sultan Qaboos Bin Said
on bilateral relations and the latest developments in the Gulf
and Middle East region, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
In the UAE, the Jordanian monarch affirmed that his visits to
the two Gulf Arab countries were aimed at discussing ways of
resolving problems and dangers facing the Arab nation through
direct dialogs.
</P>
<P>
He hinted that the Arab countries currently need a unified
position to "protect Arab rights and defend Arab causes."
</P>
<P>
"Arab states should adopt one speech to clarify to the whole
world...to safeguard our rights and defend our causes," he said in
a statement to the UAE's official Wam news agency on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
To achieve such a joint stand, "efforts should concentrate on
direct bilateral dialogs" between Arab countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that his talks with the two Gulf Arab states' leaders
are "broad-based" and cover all problems such as the stalled
Middle East peace process and the situation in the Gulf region in
the light of an Iraq-U.N. peace accord on arms inspections. 
</P>
