<HEADLINE> German Wins 10k Contest at Biathlon World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Frank Luck of Germany won a
10-kilometer biathlon World Cup event Thursday, while Olympic
champion Ole Einar Bjoerndalen of Norway came into fifth and took
the lead in overall standings in Pokljuka of slovenia.
</P>
<P>
Luck led all the way through steady rain and shot perfectly
from both prone and standing positions to score his second victory
of the season in 26 minutes, 47.5 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The German edged Raphael Poiree of France by .3 seconds, while
Russia's Viktor Maigurov finished 12.7 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Ricco Gross of Germany, who won a 20-kilogram event two days
ago and came into the race with a 10-point lead, could manage no
better than 16th place Thursday after two missed targets and had
to surrender the overall World Cup lead to Bjoerndalen.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegian now has a one-point edge, 235-234, over Gross.
</P>
