billion U.S. dollars last year, about 30 percent of the municipal's
total import and export, while its export settlement business of
8.45 billion yuan was about 50 percent of the municipal figure.
</P>
<P>
Lansheng, listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange, was Shanghai's
fourth largest export firm with 420 million U.S. dollars in
exports last year. The group made 110 million yuan in profits last
year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, BOC Shanghai had extended 500 million
yuan and 20 million U.S. dollars in loans to Lansheng. 
