<HEADLINE> China's Largest Appliance Manufacturer Expands by Buying Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Haier Group of Qingdao in
China's Shandong Province has purchased the Hefei Yellow Mountain
Electrical Co. Ltd, a major electrical appliances producer in
Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The merger can increase Haier's production capacity of
large-screen televisions to more than a million units
annually. Yellow Mountain has used technology and equipment from
the Netherlands and Japan, but bad management left it seriously in
debt.
</P>
<P>
Observers say the merger is a successful case of capital
reformation and is a good way for Haier to reach its ambitious
goal of being one of the world's top 500 multinationals.
</P>
<P>
Low-cost expansion has been a reason for the rapid growth of
Haier, which has acquired 15 domestic electrical appliance
manufacturers, acquiring 1.5 billion yuan in assets and expanding
its business from freezers, air-conditioners, and washing-machines
to televisions.
</P>
<P>
Its cooperation with the West Lake Electrical Group last
September greatly improved China's digital color TV capacity.
</P>
<P>
Haier now has 67 direct subsidiaries and 5.68 billion yuan (684
million U.S. dollars) of registered capital. It has plants in
Yugoslavia, Indonesia, Malaysia and the Philippines and more than
8,000 overseas sales outlets in North America, Europe, and the
Middle East. Sales last year topped 10.8 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
