<HEADLINE> Nankai University Makes Progress in Researches on Zhou Enlai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Nankai University, alma mater of
the late Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai, has made progress in
researches on the great statesman.
</P>
<P>
The university established China's first research center about
Zhou in 1979. To date, its experts have published hundreds of
papers and a number of academic works about Zhou's life and
thoughts.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Wang Yongxiang, director of the research center, said
that the center hosted two international seminars on Zhou
respectively in 1988 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
Zhou began his studies at Nankai University in 1919, and was
among the first group of students at the school. He is regarded as
the most outstanding alumnus of the university.
</P>
<P>
Zhou was born in Huaian City, Jiangsu Province, on March 5,
1898 and died in Beijing on January 8, 1976. 
</P>
</TEXT>
