<HEADLINE> China Marks 100th Anniversary of Zhou Enlai's Birth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Posts and
Telecommunications Administration today started selling a set of
stamps marking the 100th anniversary of China's late Premier Zhou
Enlai's birthday.
</P>
<P>
The set of four commemorative stamps, designed by two arts
professors at Nanjing Teachers' University, uses typical pictures
of Zhou, regarded as an outstanding statesman among the Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
The postal authorities of east China's Jiangsu province also
published first-day letters, stamp cards and magnetic telephone
cards of Zhou, whose birthplace was in Huai'an City of the
province.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province's department of culture today
organized a fine arts exhibition commemorating Zhou in the capital
of Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
Another photo show of Zhou also began in Guilin, southern
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
In the late 1930s, Zhou and his comrades initiated an office
for the Eighth Route Army during the War of Resistance Against
Japan from 1937 to 1945.
</P>
<P>
The Guilin government established a museum at the office's
original site in 1977. 
</P>
