<HEADLINE> Germany's Unemployment Hovering at Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Germany's jobless population remained
at a post-war record high of over 4.8 million, or 21.6 percent of
the labor force, in February.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released Thursday by the Federal Labor Office in
Nuremberg put the number of unemployed people at 4,819,400 in
February, down 3,800 from January.
</P>
<P>
The data also showed a widening gap between western and eastern
Germany, with unemployment down by 21,300 to 3,214,100 in the west
but up by 17,500 to 1,605,300 in the east.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate in western Germany was 10.4 percent in
February compared with 21.3 percent in eastern Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
