<HEADLINE> 83 HIV Positive Persons Detected in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Eighty-three HIV positive persons
have been detected in Bangladesh, State Minister for Health and
Family Welfare Mohammad Amanullah said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ten of them had full bloom of AIDS, and of those having AIDS,
six were dead, Amanullah told the Jatiya Sangsad (parliament).
</P>
<P>
The government had taken various steps to prevent the killer
disease, and had approved a national policy on HIV-AIDS related
diseases, he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that a five-year national AIDS program plan
aimed at preventing and control of the disease would be launched
on July 1 this year, and a two-year project with assistance from
the World Health Organization was already in operation in the
country.
</P>
<P>
However, the population with HIV in the country might be much
higher, according to Professor Nazrul Islam, a prominent AIDS
expert in the country. 
</P>
