<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chuan Confident of Alleviating Social Impact of Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
said Thursday that he is confident that the government will
effectively address the social problems in the country and
mitigate the social impact of the economic crisis on the people.
</P>
<P>
Chuan made the remarks at the opening ceremony of a
consultative meeting on the social impact of the economic crisis
which is co-sponsored by the Prime Minister's Office and the
United Nations Development Program.
</P>
<P>
In his address entitled "Social Impact of the Economic Crisis
and Thailand's Responses: the New Social Agenda," Chuan
highlighted the importance to establish a "people-centered" social
agenda for future development.
</P>
<P>
"To overcome this crisis..., the government and the people of
Thailand must re-examine not only its economic but also its social
agenda," he said.
</P>
<P>
"At the heart of our social agenda is the basic premise that
people are our most valuable assets and must be at the center of
all our future development endeavors."
</P>
<P>
"To make this happen, we must invest in people and provide new
opportunities to contribute to and also to benefit from future
growth," Chuan said.
</P>
<P>
Chuan said the financial crisis, which started in July 1997,
deeply affected the society and the people and shook the country's
economy.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said the increase in unemployment was one of
the most obvious social impact. Unemployment in Thailand is now
1.5 million and will possibly increase to 2 million by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Another major social impact of the crisis is the increasing
pressure on social services, especially on health and education,
Chuan said.
</P>
<P>
The government has taken steps in response to the situation,
the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
He said that a committee had been established to tackle the
unemployment problem by launching a comprehensive program
involving skill training and employment creation.
</P>
<P>
As for social service, the government vowed to maintain the
expenditure on public health and education as much as possible
despite an austerity program and necessary cuts in government
spending.
</P>
<P>
Chuan praised the sense of unity and common concern among Thai
people, describing the "Thais Help Thais" project as an example of
Thai people's positive reaction to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
With the participation of the people and the government's
commitment to good governance and a parallel decentralization of
bureaucracies, a new social agenda will be realized, Chuan said.
</P>
<P>
He also called for cooperation and collaboration with the
private sector and the international community.
</P>
<P>
"By working together, we can surely open new doors and achieve
a brighter future for Thailand -- a future in which sustainable
development is achieved not for growth in and of itself, but for
the increased welfare and prosperity of our people in the long
term," he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
