<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Produce Buick Automobiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The first batch of Shanghai-made
Buick automobiles is expected to come out at the end of this year,
today's International Trade News reported.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Buick is manufactured by the Shanghai General Motors
Corp. which receives investments from the Shanghai Automobile
Industry Corp. (SAIC) and the General Motors Corp. of the United
States. The investment, including a technology center, amounted to
1.52 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has listed Shanghai General Motors as its top project
for 1998.
</P>
<P>
The project, started last January in the Jinqiao Export
Processing District in the Pudong New Area, has so far finished
construction on five major workshops and begun to install some of
the equipment.
</P>
<P>
In April Shanghai General Motors is expected to start batch
production and plans to produce 100,000 cars a year.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning, 40 percent of the parts for Shanghai Buick
will be manufactured in China, and the figure is expected to rise
to 80 percent after three years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
