newspapers all carried editorials on Thursday, hailing the opening
of the first sessions of the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) and the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
While giving prominent coverage on the event, the Macao Daily
News said in an editorial that the current session of the NPC,
which opened on Thursday morning in Beijing, will serve as a link
between the past and future, and help pave the way for better
development in China into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"(The NPC session) will fully implement the decisions made at
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
make plans to resolve those deep-rooted problems in the economic
and political fields, thus pushing forward China's modernization
cause further along a healthy development way," said the
editorial.
</P>
<P>
Macao has five deputies attending the current NPC session. It
also has 30 members of the CPPCC National Committee. These figures
increased compared with those of the previous NPC and the CPPCC
National Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News said that the increased number of deputies
and members attending the current sessions show that the Central
Government of China are paying increased attention to Hong Kong
and Macao. It is also conducive to the smooth transition of Macao.
