<HEADLINE> Spokesman Comments on Lien Chan's 'Private Visit' to Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China today expressed "regrets and
displeasure" to the fact that relevant countries, regardless of
the repeated representations from China, insisted on receiving a
visit by Lian Chan to those countries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao made the remarks
here today when asked to comment on a report that Lian Chan of
Taiwan recently made a "private visit" to Malaysia and met with
the leaders of that country.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government firmly opposes the fact that countries
having diplomatic ties with China conduct official contact in any
form with Taiwan," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"We understand the special difficulties some Southeast Asian
countries are encountering and we hold no disagreement on the
non-governmental economic contacts between Taiwan and countries
having diplomatic ties with China," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
However, instead of an ordinary businessman, "Lien Chan is a
major political figure in Taiwan," Zhu said, adding that "the acts
by the Taiwan authorities have obvious political intent.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government asks relevant countries to respect
China's solemn stance of maintaining its national reunification,
abide by the promise they made concerning the 'one China' policy,
adopt no actions that might harm bilateral ties and safeguard the
friendly and cooperative situation between the two sides." 
</P>
