<HEADLINE> Uganda Monitors Border With Kenya over Disease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan government intensified
its border monitoring to control disease spreading in the east,
the New Vision reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Uganda Vice-President Specioza Kazibwe announced Wednesday in
house following a heavily rainy season that caused a strange
disease that kills patients within 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
Parliamentarians from eastern Uganda said six people have died
up to now. The deceased had visited Turkanaland area in western
Kenya recently.
</P>
<P>
"They died soon after returning from a visit in Turkanaland
area," said Sam Obura, a parliamentarian from Matheniko,
north-eastern district of Moroto. Matheniko division is an area
bordering Kenya.
</P>
<P>
"The government is aware of the disease," said Kazibwe, adding
that the authorities are monitoring the area and vaccinate
animals coming into the country.
</P>
<P>
A team of health, agricultural experts and local officials has
been sent to the scene to identify the nature of the disease and
try to control the situation, the vice-president revealed.
</P>
</TEXT>
