<HEADLINE> Chinese Oceanic Information Network Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese oceanic information
network has become operational recently with a Chinese and English
web site on the Internet, according to the State Oceanic
Administration.
</P>
<P>
Browsers can access the network by visiting the web site at
nmdis.go.cn on the Internet. The network provides an information
search, browsing through data, and other services. It also can
offer on-line date transmission for oceanic information systems.
</P>
<P>
Chinese oceanic departments and industries can take advantage
of the network to make them known to the rest of the
world, using multi-media technology. They can also exchange
information and discuss marine scientific problems with their
foreign counterparts through the net. 
</P>
</TEXT>
