<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive on Rostrum of Ninth NPC Opening Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee-hwa, chief executive of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), attended the
opening session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC),
China's new legislature, as a non-voting delegate this morning.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time in history that Hong Kong, which returned
to the motherland on July 1 last year, has sent its head of
government to an annual session of the country's paramount body of
state power.
</P>
<P>
At 8:35 a.m., Tung, in spick-and-span dark suit, was energetic
and beamed with smiles as he came to a lounge at the southern side
of the Great Hall of the People, venue of the NPC session.
</P>
<P>
He came across Defense Minister Chi Haotian and Jiang Enzhu,
head of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch at the gate, who
greeted him with cordial handshakes and an exchange of greetings.
Several photographers aside snapped the scene.
</P>
<P>
Then he sat down beside Wan Guoquan, vice-chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), China's top advisory body, and they had a
hearty conversation.
</P>
<P>
In the lounge, Wang Guangying, an executive chairman of the NPC
session's Presidium, noticing Tung's arrival, rose from his seat
and greeted the chief executive with a cordial handshake.
</P>
<P>
Almost all new arrivers at the lounge shook hands with this
honored guest invited to the session by the Standing Committee of
the Eighth NPC.
</P>
<P>
When the bell sounded a few minutes before the NPC session
began, President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng and other top
government leaders, who had been in the other side of the lounge,
walked over to meet Tung and greeted him with cordial handshakes.
</P>
<P>
In the conference hall, Tung was seated on the right flank of
the third row on the rostrum, with Wan Guoquan and Luo Haocai,
chairman of the Central Committee of the China Zhi Gong Party, one
of China's eight non-Communist parties, sitting next to him.
</P>
<P>
When Li Peng was reading out his government work report, Tung
listened attentively and was seen occasionally marking the lines
with a pencil.
</P>
<P>
When asked about his idea on the current NPC session upon his
arrival in Beijing on Wednesday evening, Tung said it is convened
at the time China is facing major growth opportunities, and that
it will surely contribute to the trans-century development and
prosperity for the country.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong SAR has sent a delegation of 35 deputies to the
ongoing NPC session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
