<HEADLINE> Mongolia Promoting Coal Mine Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia is eyeing foreign
funds and equipments to promote its coal mine industry.
</P>
<P>
Advanced coal-mining equipments worth of 14.6 million
U.S. dollars from the United States was introduced Tuesday to
transform its biggest coal mine factory, 120 kilometers away from
Ulan Bator.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia will receive a 35-million-dollar long-term preferential
loan to step up the exploitation of the coal mine industry from
the World Bank under an agreement reached by the two sides,
according to the Mongolian government.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese government also will provide Mongolia
with long-term preferential loan worth of 5.8 billion Yuan (46.4
million dollars) to help promote the resource-rich country,
official source said.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia's coal reserves of the 200 already-exploited coal
mines reach 15.2 billion ton, while the coal output last
year only registered 4.95 million ton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
