<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Bringing Big Change In Central Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The influx of increasing amounts
of overseas investment in central China's Henan Province has given
the local economy a new look.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the province had 5,794 overseas-funded
enterprises, with seven billion US dollars worth of overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
The money has helped speed up local infrastructure
construction. Nearly 1.2 billion US dollars of overseas investment
has been used for 38 Sino-foreign joint power plants, which have a
combined capacity of 3.9 million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
The majority of highways built in recent years were funded by
overseas governments and financial institutions. Henan now has
more than 400 km of expressways.
</P>
<P>
The growth of overseas-funded businesses has provided a large
number of employment opportunities for local people, and they
employ nearly 300,000 people.
</P>
<P>
A number of state companies have been transformed and improved
by the use of overseas funding and have been turned into larger
businesses.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-backed businesses are mostly involved in light
industry, textiles, machinery, electronics, chemicals,
pharmaceuticals, metallurgy, building materials, agriculture, real
estate, telecommunications, and tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
