<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1500-Year-Old Human Skeleton Found in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Archaeologists have
uncovered the 1500-year-old skeleton of a young woman on the
excavated site of a proposed shopping mall outside Nelspruit,
about 400 km northeast of Johannesburg, local daily Sowetan
reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
University of the Witwatersrand archaeologist Tom Huffman said
bulldozers on the mall site had exposed the skeleton of a yound
woman, aged between 16 and 24. Her leg and pelvic bones had been
crushed by the bulldozers.
</P>
<P>
Another important finding, two cattle kraals near the woman,
put to rest a 20-year-old debate about whether the system of
lobola was practiced in the early Iron Age.
</P>
<P>
"This proves that cattle and lobola, which is the system of
exchanging wives for cattle, were an important part of society in
the early Iron Age," Huffman was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said it was known that cattle were important in society
1,000 years ago because cattle bones were abundant at sites
dating from that time, but there were few cattle bones from the
early Iron Age.
</P>
<P>
"This latest find raises a new issue, however, and that is of
the climatic conditions of the area in 500 AD," Huffman said,
noting the remains of grass in cattle dung found in two food pits
at the Nelspruit site were not the same as grass found in the
area today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Computer Joint Venture Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The formation of a
Sino-U.S. computer company was announced in Fuzhou, capital of
east China's Fujian Province, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Shidi Computer Co, jointly established by China's Star Computer
Group Co. Ltd (SCGC) and Digital Corp. from the United States,
will produce Digital's Pentium II, a desk-top computer and server.
</P>
<P>
Digital will provide 51 percent of the first-phase investment
of 30 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to begin operation in the second quarter this year,
the joint venture plans to sell most of its products on the
domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1980, the Fuzhou-based SCGC now has total assets
of 1.6 billion yuan, listed No. 35 in the country's electronics
sector.
</P>
<P>
Digital, which began business 40 years ago, is capable of
completing 13 billion U.S. dollars annually in sales
volume. 
</P>
</TEXT>
