<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese VCD Industry Growing Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The video compact disc (VCD)
industry of China has witnessed explosive growth during the past
three years, becoming a major money-maker for China's electronics
industry.
</P>
<P>
China produced more than 10 million VCD players last year. The
VCD industry, with a sales volume of 20 billion yuan in 1997,
employs some 20 million people.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Ministry of Internal Trade show that, the
number of VCD players sold in the country's major department
stores last year was 10 times the figure of 1996.
</P>
<P>
More than 12 percent of households in Beijing, Tianjin and
Shanghai own VCD players. Domestic VCD players account for 87
percent of the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
While Chinese-made VCD players are expanding their share of
this emerging market, their prices have also dropped dramatically
during the last three years.
</P>
<P>
A VCD player sold for more than 4,000 yuan in 1995, 2,800 yuan
at the beginning of 1996, 1,700 yuan at the end of 1996, and
finally, to 1,200 yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict tougher competition in the VCD market this
year, but that the sector will continue to have good market
prospects.
</P>
<P>
They urged VCD manufacturers to improve technology and
establish better brand-name identification.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
