<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australians Getting Fatter: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Australians are becoming fatter
with more than half of the male population and almost half of
females overweight, a workshop held in Perth, a southwestern port
city, was told Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The workshop, organized by the National Heart Foundation, is
based on a recently released report, which found 63 percent of
Australian men and 47 percent of Australian women were overweight,
Australian Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The report, by the National Health and Medical Research
Council, states that Australians have gained two to three
kilograms in the last decade, despite spending an estimated 500
million Australian dollars (340 million U.S. dollars) a year on
diets and weight loss products.
</P>
<P>
National Heart Foundation health promotion director Trevor
Shilton blamed an increasingly sedentary lifestyle for the weight
gain.
</P>
<P>
"The motor car and other labor saving devices mean that over
half the community do not take sufficient daily physical activity
to benefit their health," he said.
</P>
<P>
Health, education, transport and local government
representatives attended the workshop, which was reported to
generate a range of recommendations to prevent further weight gain
in adults.
</P>
<P>
These recommendations, combined with recommendations that come
from workshops in other states, will be presented to the federal
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya, UNEP Reach Data Communication Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government and the
United Nations Environment Program (UNEP) have reached an
agreement on the use of the Mercure Satellite Communication
System, UNEP Executive Director Klaus Topfer was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The UNEP boss said Wednesday that the agreement would require
UNEP to pay Kenya 150,000 U.S. Dollars each year for data
transmission services and maintenance of the system.
</P>
<P>
"This is a very, very positive step forward after two-and-half
years of discussions," said Topfer, adding that it was of "vital
importance" that another agreement be worked out to integrate
voice transmission into the system.
</P>
<P>
He noted that unless the new UNEP management proved they could
work in Nairobi cost-effectively, the location of a United
Nations office here could prove a burden.
</P>
<P>
UNEP can only maximize its efficiency if it is able to
establish communication links with other environmental
organizations worldwide, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Executive Director pointed out that some of the
organization's main donors had so far invested 15 million Dollars
while UNEP itself had put in a further 5 million Dollars into the
installation of the system.
</P>
<P>
The Mercure network which is the Global Internet for
Environment and Sustainable Development will provide UNEP with a
modern global communications capability for the transfer and
exchange of environmental and administrative data between its
regional centers and the globally distributed environmental
databases and archives of its many partners.
</P>
<P>
The network will make it possible for environmental centers in
developing countries and countries in Central and Eastern Europe
to obtain timely access to environmental data which include maps
and images acquired from environmental satellites and a wide
variety of other sources.
</P>
<P>
Before Mercure came into existence, environmental data was
transmitted through inefficient and expensive long distance
telephone lines and by time-consuming mail deliveries or courier
services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
