<HEADLINE> Agassi Advances to Arizona Quarters, Kiefer Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Andre Agassi of the United
States continued his form on Wednesday when he moved into the
quarter-finals of the Franklin templeton Classic in Scottsdale,
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The former number one disposed of Nicolas Lapentti of Ecuador
7-5, 6-1 in just 62 minutes.
</P>
<P>
But the American started slowly as he just avoided a
tie-breaker to win the first set, but he wasted no time to wrap up
a big win, which Agassi viewed as the most memorable one in his
pro life.
</P>
<P>
In another match of the day, fourth seed Nicolas Kiefer of
Germany was blitzed by American qualifier Jan-Michael Gambill in
just 55 minutes, 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Gambill cannoned six successive aces in the second set and
eliminated the 28th-ranked German on five breaks.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Albert Costa of Spain overpowered Sargis Sargsian
of Armenia to enter the quarter-finals, 6-3, 3-6, 6-1, and
Dutchman Sjeng Schalken outlasted eighth-seed Richard Fromberg of
Australia 4-6, 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-0). 
</P>
