<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0214 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Major Policy Bank Sets Quarterly Loan Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank of
China (SDB), one of the nation's three policy-oriented financial
institutions, plans to issue 12.2 billion yuan (about 1.4 billion
U.S. dollars) in loans in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The loan budget has been officially approved by the appropriate
departments, the Shanghai Securities News reported today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 12 billion yuan will be invested in more than 200
infrastructure projects, including the Shanghai Pudong Airport and
Ertan Power Station.
</P>
<P>
China phased out its loan quota system among commercial banks
on Jan. 1, but the practice is still applied to SDB and the other
two policy banks -- the Import and Export Bank of China and the
Agricultural Development Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
SDB, set up in 1994 to fund large infrastructure projects,
extended 107.7 billion yuan in loans in 1997, and this year it
plans to issue 95 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
