<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austrian Painter's Works to be Displayed in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-one representative
paintings of famous Austrian artist Max Weiler will be on display
in the China Art Gallery March 10-April 7.
</P>
<P>
As part of the '98 China Year of International Fine Arts
(CYIFA) series, the exhibition will be organized by China's
Ministry of Culture and the Austrian Foreign Ministry, and
presented by the China International Exhibition Agency (CIEA) and
China Art Gallery.
</P>
<P>
Finland-based Nokia Group is the major sponsor.
</P>
<P>
CIEA Director Hao Zhan said in a news conference here today
that the exhibition is not only an important part of CYIFA, but
also a major event in cultural exchanges between China and Austria.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Vice-Chancellor and Foreign Minister Wolfgang
Schuessel who arrived in Beijing this morning to start his
official visit to China as a guest of his Chinese counterpart,
Qian Qichen, will also attend the opening ceremony and
ribbon-cutting.
</P>
<P>
Born in 1910, Weiler is one of the most famous modern painters
in Austria, He traveled extensively in Europe and America
designing frescoes for world-renowned architecture.
</P>
<P>
Weiler held or participated in more than 30 exhibitions and won
numerous prizes and honorary titles during his 50-year painting
career.
</P>
<P>
Exhibiting works in Beijing is a long-cherished wish of Weiler,
88, who identified himself with principles he found in Chinese
landscape painting of the Song Dynasty (960-1279).
</P>
<P>
The artist combined the Chinese style with modern European
abstract art and created a unique painting style.
</P>
<P>
The works on display were painted between 1983 and 1992.
</P>
<P>
These works, mainly from the Vienna Art History Museum and
private collections from other countries, are considered among his
best. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0218 </DOCNO>
