<HEADLINE> China's Standard Of Living Is Improving Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China is one of a few countries
that have had a rapid improvement in the standard of living,
thanks to the country's reforms, opening up, and modernization
drive.
</P>
<P>
According to the State Statistics Bureau, in 1997, per-capita
income was 5,140 yuan for urban residents and 2,080 yuan for rural
people, up 2.9 percent and 4 percent respectively from the
previous year, when adjusted for inflation.
</P>
<P>
From 1993 to 1996, average annual growth in consumer spending
was 7.6 percent, according to the official figures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
