<HEADLINE> Chongqing Seeks to Attract More Foreign Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China's most populous
municipality, Chongqing, has expressed a wish to enhance
cooperation with overseas businesses.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing mayor Pu Haiqing told Xinhua that he would hope to
get support from international companies to help build the city
into a regional economic center on the upper reaches of the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The city's foreign investment surged following its change in
status from a provincial city to a city directly under the central
government in March of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The city attracted 3.6 billion U.S. dollars in contracted
foreign investment and has actually used 940 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi, Siemens, Mobil and other big companies headed the
rush of foreign investment into the city, which has an area of
82,000 square kilometers and a population of 30 million.
</P>
<P>
The city is endowed with rich agricultural, mineral and water
resources. Construction of the nearby Three Gorges project also
makes the city more appealing for foreign investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
