<BODY>
<HEADLINE> DPRK Press Marks Zhou Enlai Centenary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Rodong Sinmun, the official
newspaper of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK),
said Thursday that the DPRK people bear in mind the great efforts
by late Chinese premier Zhou Enlai in the development of the
DPRK-China friendship.
</P>
<P>
Marking the centenary of the birth of Zhou Thursday, the Rodong
Sinmun highly praised Zhou for making remarkable achievements in
the causes of liberation of the Chinese people, the construction
of socialism and the enhancement of DPRK-China friendship.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that as one of the key members of the
China's leadership, Zhou was a prominent and experienced
revolutionist, politician, strategist and diplomat.
</P>
<P>
Zhou's sincerity to the Chinese revolution and the Communist
Party of China (CPC) and his accomplishment were still encouraging
the Chinese people to stride on the road of national construction,
it said.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, the Chinese people unite closely around the CPC
headed by Jiang Zemin and are working hard for the construction of
socialism with Chinese characteristics and the modernization of
the country, it said.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK people were glad to see the Chinese people making
progress in their cause of construction and wished them complete
success, it added.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the further promotion of DPRK-China
friendship, fostered by late leaders of the two countries, was not
only in the interests of the two peoples, but conducive to world
peace and development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
