<HEADLINE> First Session of Ninth NPC Opens in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC) opened this morning in the Great
Hall of the People in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
A total 2,440 deputies from 32 provinces, autonomous regions
and centrally-administered municipalities, from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region and the People's Liberation Army,
attended the opening meeting.
</P>
<P>
The session will elect people for the following posts for new
terms of office: president of the country, chairman of the Central
Military Commission, chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Ninth NPC, president of the Supreme People's Court, and
procurator-general of the Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of nominations by the president of the country,
the session will decide on the new premier and members of the
State Council, China's highest governing body.
</P>
<P>
Another important item on the agenda of the session is to
deliberate on a Plan Concerning Institutional Restructuring of the
State Council.
</P>
<P>
The Second Plenary Meeting of the 15th Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China, held last month, emphasized that
institutional restructuring is a requirement of deepening economic
reform and a developing socialist market economy, that it is
needed to cement relations between the Party and government on one
side and the people on the other, and that it is a component of
political reform.
</P>
<P>
At nine o'clock, Tian Jiyun, an executive chairman of the
presidium of the session, announced the meeting open.
</P>
<P>
At five past nine, Premier Li Peng began to deliver a
Government Work Report on behalf of the State Council, which
consists of three parts: government work over the past five years,
suggestions on government work in 1998, and international
situation and China's diplomatic work.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, decisive strides have been made in
economic restructuring, and implementation of the open policy has
reached a new level, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Social productive forces in China, the country's overall
national strength and the standard of living of the Chinese people
have been brought to a new stage of development. Hong Kong has
successfully returned to the motherland. National unity and social
stability have been further consolidated," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Session of Ninth NPC Opens in Beijing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The past five years constitute a good period in the development
of the People's Republic. During this period, China enjoyed
political stability and unity among the people, developed all
businesses and increased its national strength, Li Peng said.
</P>
<P>
"To sum up, the basic experience we have gained over the past
five years is to hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory, conscientiously carry out the basic line of the Communist
Party of China for the primary stage of socialism, persist in
making economic development our central task, adhere to the Four
Cardinal Principles, persevere in reform and opening to the
outside world and unswervingly advance along the road to socialism
with Chinese characteristics. This is the basic guarantee for
overcoming all difficulties and obstacles and continuing to
advance in all our undertakings," the premier said.
</P>
<P>
About suggestions on government work in 1998, Li Peng said that
this year is the first year of implementing the spirit of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China in an all-round
way and an important year for promoting reform, opening to the
outside world and the modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Through careful discussion and solicitation of views from all
quarters, the State Council now puts forward the following
suggestions on government work in 1998: further stabilize and
strengthen agriculture; make new breakthroughs in reform of
state-owned enterprises; continue to strengthen and improve
macro-controls; do better in opening to the outside world; develop
science, technology, education and cultural undertakings; strive
to improve material and cultural conditions for people in urban
and rural areas; actively restructure government institutions; and
promote the great cause of peaceful reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
On the international situation and China's diplomatic work, Li
Peng said the Chinese government has all along maintained that
state-to-state relations should be established on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence and that disputes should
be settled peacefully through consultations on an equal footing.
</P>
<P>
"Resolutely opposed to hegemonism in whatever form, China is
forever an important force contributing to world peace and
regional stability. The Chinese government and people are ready to
work with all other governments and peoples of the world to make
their due contribution to establishing a peaceful, stable, just
and equitable new international political and economic order and
to promoting the lofty cause of world peace and development," Li
Peng said.
</P>
<P>
Li's speech was frequently interrupted by applauses.
</P>
<P>
High-ranking leaders Jiang Zemin, Qiao Shi, Zhu Rongji, Li
Ruihuan, Liu Huaqing, Wei Jianxing, Li Lanqing and Rong Yiren were
seated on the rostrum.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 members of the Ninth National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
attended the meeting as observers. Ambassadors of foreign
countries in China were invited to the meeting, and hundreds of
Chinese and foreign reporters came to cover the opening meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Central People's Broadcast Station, the China Central
Television Station and China Radio International made live
broadcast of the opening meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
