<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Complete Armed Forces Reduction on Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China will complete on schedule
the task of reducing its armed forces by 500,000 persons within
three years, Premier Li Peng announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Li made the announcement in his government work report to the
First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) which
will last till March 19.
</P>
<P>
The current reduction of armed forces was announced by Party
General Secretary Jiang Zemin at the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) held last September.
</P>
<P>
In his report, Li also urged local governments at various
levels to make proper arrangements in placing demobilized
servicemen to be transferred to civilian work and give strong
backing to the strengthening and reform of the People's Liberation
Army (PLA) and support the army in its efforts to improve itself
and take the road appropriate to China towards fewer but better
troops.
</P>
<P>
The current reduction of armed forces is the ninth in the PLA's
history. Up to seven million troops of the Chinese armed forces
have been reduced over the 49 years since new China was founded in
1949.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
