<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Ten Million Needy People to Shake Off Poverty: Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- More than ten million needy people
in China's rural areas will have adequate food and clothing this
year, Premier Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
In his s Government Work Report at the openning session of the
Ninth NPC, Li said that in 1978, there were 250 million
impoverished people in the countryside, who accounted for one
quarter of the people in need around the world.
</P>
<P>
Along with China's reform and opening-up and poverty
alleviation by the government, the population of the poor in the
rural areas became 65 million in 1995, who took up one-twentieth
of the world's poor people.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, 15 million people shook off poverty.
As a result, the number of the impoverished has been reduced to 50
million.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China and the Chinese government have
announced that all the needy in the rural areas will have adequate
food and clothes by the end of the century. Consequently, many
measures have been taken for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
In his report, Li Peng called on local governments to further
strengthen their leadership in anti-poverty work, increase input,
improve conditions for production in impoverished areas, and
support the development of planting, breeding, forestry, fruit
growing and the processing of agricultural and sideline products
which directly provide the needy with adequate food and clothing.
</P>
<P>
Assistance should be provided especially to villages and
households that are exceedingly poor and needy, Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Authorities Urged for Early Negotiations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua)--The reunification of China is an
irreversible historical trend and the Taiwan question will surely
be resolved, Li Peng, premier of the State Council, said today.
</P>
<P>
In his government work report delivered at the First Session of
the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), Li Peng said: "We hope
that the Taiwan authorities respond as early as possible to our
solemn appeal that the two sides conduct political negotiations
under the principle of one China."
</P>
<P>
"Taiwan is an inalienable part of the inviolable territory of
China," Li said.
</P>
<P>
"We will as always adhere to the basic principles of 'peaceful
reunification' and 'one country, two systems' and to the
eight-point proposal put forward by President Jiang Zemin on
developing cross-Strait relations and promoting the peaceful
reunification of the motherland," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will spare no efforts in expanding exchanges and
cooperation between the two sides of the Taiwan Strait in
economic, scientific, technological and cultural areas and promote
mutual visits of people," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will make joint efforts with our compatriots in Taiwan to
firmly oppose any splittist activities aimed at bringing about the
'independence of Taiwan' and creating 'two Chinas' or 'one China,
one Taiwan'," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng expressed the hope that the Taiwan authorities take
into consideration the overall interests of the Chinese nation and
the fundamental interests of the people in Taiwan, take concrete
steps for the early establishment of direct links of postal, air
and shipping services and trade between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
"Taiwan's future hinges on the reunification of the
motherland," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
