<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Petroleum Revenues Fall in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Compared to January 1997, the
Central Bank of Venezuela's income was reduced by 560 million
U.S. dollars in January this year as a result of a decline in
petroleum income.
</P>
<P>
The decline in revenue was attributed to a reduction in
petroleum prices on international markets beginning last December,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The petroleum price plunge, which affected the net income
received by the Central Bank, has caused a reduction in the
national budget of about 1.3 billion dollars. The petroleum
budget in Venezuela has also been affected.
</P>
<P>
The oil price was 16 dollars per barrel before December 1997.
The average price of crude oil in January was 13.05 dollars per
barrel and 12.18 dollars in February, the Ministry of Energy and
Mines said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
