<HEADLINE> Premier Reiterates China's Stance on Iraq Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China holds that the memorandum of
understanding reached between the UN secretary-general Kofi Annan
and the Iraqi government should be carried out to the letter.
</P>
<P>
These remarks came from Premier Li Peng in his government work
report at the opening session of the NPC, China's top legislature,
here today.
</P>
<P>
Li said China highly appreciates the mediation efforts by
UN secretary-general Annan for the peaceful solution of the
Iraqi weapons inspections crisis.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government has maintained that relations between
countries should be based on the Five Principles of Peaceful
Co-existence, and that all disputes should be settled peacefully
through equal consultations instead of resorting to the use of
force or military threats," Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, China resolutely opposes hegemonism of any
form and will serve permanently as an important force in
maintaining world peace and regional stability. 
</P>
