<HEADLINE> Anti-Child Labor March Arrives in Uruguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A 30-man group arrived in
Uruguay today on their second leg of a pan-American march against
child labor.
</P>
<P>
The marchers come from different Latin American countries and
are trying to call governments' attention to child labor in their
tour across the American continent.
</P>
<P>
The group began their march on Rio de Janeiro on Wednesday and
will march to Argentina, Chile, Paraguay and other countries in
the continent.
</P>
<P>
The march is part of a global action protest against child
labor. In Asia, a march began from Manila on January 17 and in
Africa, a march will begin on March 21.
</P>
<P>
There are 250 million children in labor worldwide. 
</P>
