<HEADLINE> Brazilian Vehicle Sales Drop in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A total of 103,284 vehicles
were sold in Brazil in February, a decrease of 4.4 percent
compared with January.
</P>
<P>
The February figure was a 26 percent drop against February of
1997.
</P>
<P>
The Italian Fiat and the United States Ford sold 24,448 and
14,053 units last month, declining by 24.4 percent and 8.2 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, Volkswagen sold 33,5750 vehicles in February, becoming
the largest car seller in Brazil, increasing by 5.2 percent over
January.
</P>
<P>
Sales by the U.S. General Motors went up by 4.1 percent over
January. 
