<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier on Achievements in Past Five Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- In his government work report he
delivered here today at the first session of the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC), Chinese Premier Li Peng said China has
made tremendous achievements in socialist modernization in the
last five years.
</P>
<P>
Decisive strides have been made in economic restructuring, and
implementation of the government's open policy has reached a new
level in the last five years, he said.
</P>
<P>
The past five years constitute a fairly good period of
development since the founding of New China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Social productive forces, the overall national strength and the
standard of living of the Chinese people have all reached a new
level, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has successfully returned to the embrace of the
motherland, and national unity and social stability have been
further consolidated, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, China's economy has maintained a good
momentum of growth and the economic strength of the country has
increased substantially. In 1997, China's gross domestic product
reached 7.477 trillion yuan. Economic growth in the last five
years averaged 11 percent on average as calculated in terms of
comparable prices, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The country fulfilled the government's Eighth Five-Year Plan
and attained ahead of schedule the goal of quadrupling the 1980
GDP by the end of the century. It has brought inflation under
effective control.
</P>
<P>
Major breakthroughs have been made in reform that aims to
establish a socialist market economy; a framework for a new
macro-control system has been erected preliminarily; and the
fundamental role of the market in the allocation of resources has
been notably bolstered, he said.
</P>
<P>
China has continued an all-direction, multilevel and wide-range
opening to the outside world. The volume of China's annual import
and export has increased from 165.5 billion U.S. dollars to 325.1
billion U.S. dollars over the last five years, he said.
</P>
<P>
Actual funds from direct foreign investment totaled 185.8
billion U.S. dollars over the past five years. National foreign
exchange reserves have gone up from 19.4 billion U.S. dollars to
139.9 billion U.S. dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
Science and technology, education, and cultural undertakings
have made progresses; and so has work to promote socialist
ideological and ethical progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to develop socialist democracy and improve the legal
system have been reinforced, ethnic unity and social stability
further consolidated, and progresses made in modernizing defense
and the army, he said.
</P>
<P>
Incomes of the urban and rural populations have increased
significantly and people's standard of living has improved, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
