<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Becker to Skip Indian Wells </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker, who has been
plagued by injury, has decided to turn down a wild-card entry
offer for the Indian Well tennis tournament next week.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old former world No. 1 from Germany, withdraw from
this week's event at Scottsdale because of a back injury.
</P>
<P>
The German champion, who has slumped to 66 in the rankings,
also withdrew from last month's ATP Tour event in Dubai after
tearing an abdominal muscle. And he also missed last week's
tournament in Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
Becker spent Tuesday visited a Phoenix Spine specialist and had
a computer scan on his back. The test ruled out a herniated disc
problem.
</P>
<P>
Since the start of 1997, Becker has pulled out of 11 events
because of injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
