<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Future Sure to Be More Promising: Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's future is bound to be
still brighter, since its return to the motherland has had a good
beginning, Premier Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark while delivering the Government Work Report
at the opening ceremony of the First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC), which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong to the motherland is both a great
victory for the Chinese nation and a great event that had drawn
worldwide attention. It has put an end to the century-old
humiliation of the Chinese nation and activated the national
spirit and we are very proud of it," Li said.
</P>
<P>
The smooth transition in Hong Kong is a great success
attributable to Deng Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two
systems" and will facilitate the return of Macao to the motherland
and the resolution of the Taiwan question, all with a view to
achieving the complete reunification of the motherland, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the past eight months since Hong Kong's return, its previous
socio-economic system and way of life have remained unchanged and
its laws have been kept basically unchanged. The policies of "one
country, two systems", and "Hong Kong people administering Hong
Kong" with a high degree of autonomy, and the Basic Law of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region have been implemented in
an all-round way, the premier said.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong now enjoys social stability, its residents have a
sense of security and its economy is developing smoothly," Li Peng
said.
</P>
<P>
"The central government has given full support to the
government of Hong Kong SAR in its work and in the measures it has
taken for dealing with the impact of the financial crises in
Southeast Asian countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he is pleased to see that, as an independent
constituency, Hong Kong SAR has elected deputies to attend this
Congress and participate in the administration of state affairs.
</P>
</TEXT>
