<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Sums Up Five-Year Experience (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng summed up the experience
of the fruitful government work in the last five years during his
last term as the Chinese premier at the First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC), which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
He said the basic experience is to hold high the great banner
of Deng Xiaoping Theory, conscientiously carry out the basic line
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) for the primary stage of
socialism, persist in making economic development our central
task, adhere to the Four Cardinal Principles, persevere in the
reform and opening to the outside world and unswervingly advance
along the road to socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"This is the basic guarantee for overcoming all difficulties
and obstacles and continuing to advance in all our undertakings,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
In reviewing the work of the government in the past five years,
Li has formulated the following ideas:
</P>
<P>
-- First, adhere to the ideological line of emancipating the
minds and seeking truth from facts;
</P>
<P>
-- Second, balance reform, development and stability;
</P>
<P>
-- Third, give full play to the role of the market mechanism
and strengthen and improve macroeconomic control;
</P>
<P>
-- Fourth, implement the strategies of developing the
country by relying on science and education and of achieving
sustainable development;
</P>
<P>
-- Fifth, adhere to the principle of doing two types of work at
the same time, attaching equal importance to both.
</P>
<P>
In its efforts to carry out reform, opening up and the
modernization drive, he said, China will proceed from the actual
situation of being in a primary stage of socialism and take its
own road.
</P>
<P>
"We should assimilate all advances of other countries but
not blindly follow what the books say, nor can we mechanically
imitate other countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should break away from old concepts, respect the people's
pioneering spirit, make bold experiments and actively explore the
way forward," he continued.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time, we should act in accordance with objective
laws, correctly appraise situations and strive for practical
results," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
