<HEADLINE> Blijlevens Wins First Stage in Murcia Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Jeroen Blijlevens of Netherlands
sprinted to win the first stage of the Tour of Murcia cycling race
in Jumilla, Spain on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Blijlevens outsprinted his rivals at the end of the
144-kilometer stage, followed by second jann Kirsipuu of Estonia
and third Endrio Leoni of Italy.
</P>
<P>
It was Blijlevens's first stage win of the season. 
</P>
