<BODY>
<HEADLINE> January Unemployment Rate Hits New High in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The average unemployment rate in
Brazil shot up to a 7.25 percent in January, the highest rate for
the month since 1985.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate was up from 4.84 percent in December 1997,
according to the Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's six biggest cities had recorded the sharpest rises,
contributing most to the national unemployment figure.
</P>
<P>
The largest city, Sao Paulo, had the highest unemployment rate
with 8.51 percent.
</P>
<P>
Salvador, capital of Bahia state in the northeast, was the only
region with no recorded increase in the number of unemployed.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has a workforce of around 70 million out of a population
of 160 million population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
