<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Stabilize and Strengthen Agriculture, Says Li Peng (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to take
effective measures to ensure another good harvest, increase
peasants' incomes and maintain social stability in rural areas,
said Premier Li Peng today.
</P>
<P>
In his government work report given to the First Session of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), which opened here today,
Li said, "Agriculture has a direct bearing on our overall
situation. We should never neglect agriculture because of good
harvests over the years or because there is an adequate supply of
agricultural products."
</P>
<P>
In 1998, China plans to produce 492.5 billion kg of grain, four
million tons of cotton, both of which match the 1997 figures.
</P>
<P>
With a view to the market as our orientation, he said China will
readjust and optimize the structure of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
According to the premier, the Chinese government will take
the initiative to promote an industrial management of agriculture,
widen the channels of distribution, integrate the production,
processing and marketing of agricultural products and have all
these factors support each other to ensure that peasants can
derive income from production and benefit from the processing and
marketing of their products.
</P>
<P>
Reforming the grain purchasing and marketing system is an
important task in 1998 and we should go about this
conscientiously, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng also addressed the importance of the role of science
and technology for increasing agricultural output.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to strengthen the agricultural
infrastructure, Li said. Different measures will be taken in line
with different conditions and priorities emphasized in water
conservancy construction projects.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0288 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Stabilize and Strengthen Agriculture, Says Li Peng (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the south, he said China will concentrate on preventing
floods, and in the north the country will concentrate on fighting
droughts.
</P>
<P>
China will tighten control over water resources and implement
the system of charging for their use to encourage more economical
consumption, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li urged governments at all levels to increase investment in
agriculture, guarantee water conservancy construction funds and
encourage farmers and rural collectives to increase their input
through labor and investment.
</P>
<P>
He told the NPC delegates that the Chinese government will
redouble its efforts to increase farmland improvement projects,
plant trees and grass, control soil erosion and improve conditions
for agricultural production and the ecology.
</P>
<P>
It will strictly control the land used for urban and rural
construction projects, implement a basic farmland protection
system and attend to the protection of arable land in earnest,
he said.
</P>
<P>
China will also promote the development of town and township
enterprises, especially those in the central and western parts of
the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should keep stable the household responsibility contract
system with remuneration linked to output, carry out the policy of
prolonging the land contract period for another 30 years and
earnestly endeavor to lighten the burden on farmers," he said.
</P>
<P>
In rural areas, he noted that China will strengthen political
power at the grass-roots level and self-government organizations
of the villagers and improve relations between cadres and the
masses. All this is an important guarantee for developing the
rural economy and maintaining rural stability, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
