<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Deputies Satisfied with Economic Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese legislators attending the
First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) that
opens today say that they are extremely satisfied with the
country's current economic situation.
</P>
<P>
"In the past five years, the Chinese economy has recorded the
most rapid and sound growth in history," said Xie Qingjian, a
deputy to the Ninth NPC from east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The current fine economic situation of high growth and low
inflation indicates that the incumbent Chinese government is
highly competent and all measures it has taken to develop economy
are successful, added Xie, president of the Zhejiang Provincial
Branch of the People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
"Now that the socialist market economic system has taken
initial shape in China and new reform steps are expected to be
taken in the economic field, I confide in our country's future,"
he noted.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Houjian, an NPC deputy from Qingdao, a coastal city in
east China's Shandong Province, said it's a miracle that China
last year scored a high economic growth of 8.8 percent while
successfully controlling inflation.
</P>
<P>
President of Hi-sense, a successful hi-tech enterprise, Zhou
attributed the fast development of his company in recent years to
China's favorable macro-economic environment, as well as reforms
of tax and foreign trade systems, unified exchange rate,
rectification of financial order and low inflation.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yumei, a 25-year-old female farmer from Shandong, is now
running a conglomerate specialized in rabbit breeding, with annual
profits of more than 6.5 million yuan (783,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
"Without the policy that encourages the growth of private
business, it would have been impossible for me to make a fortune
by raising rabbits. And my enterprise won't be so successful
without the fine economic situation in these years," she
acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
Yuen Mo, a deputy from the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region which returned to China on July 1 last year, said that he
was deeply impressed by the tremendous economic achievements of
the interior areas over recent years.
</P>
<P>
"It's already not easy to provide ample food and clothing for
more than 1.2 billion people. It's more amazing at high growth and
low inflation that have been scored for the national economy.
I'm really proud of my motherland," he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
