<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Killed, Two Injured in New Jersey Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and two
others injured when a small plane crashed into an apartment
building in New Jersey Wednesday, the United Press International
reported.
</P>
<P>
National Transportation Safety Board spokesman Bob Pearce was
quoted as saying that the dead victims were aboard the twin-engine
Piper Apache and that the injured parties were on the ground.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred around 2:20 p.m. EDT (1920 GMT) at the
Brookside Lane apartment complex. It was not immediately known
where the plane was coming from and where it was going.
</P>
<P>
The NTSB and the Federal Aviation Administration were
investigating the accident and were trying to determine the number
of passengers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
