<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Rural Development Project in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced
Wednesday the approval of a 20.5 million U.S. dollar loan to
Indonesia for the Bengkulu regional development project to promote
rural economic growth there.
</P>
<P>
This project will introduce new agricultural technologies and
improve village infrastructure to increase farm incomes and living
standards for nearly 40,000 households in 220 villages in
Bengkulu, Sumartra's second poorest province.
</P>
<P>
The village councils will manage village grants to be provided
under the project, to implement the two main components of the
project. One is for village-based adoption of agricultural
technologies and the other is for construction of village
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 25.7 million
dollars. In addition to the World Bank loan, 2.7 million dollars
will come from the participating farmers which will be contributed
in the form of labor and the remaining 2.6 million dollars from
the Indonesian government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
