<HEADLINE> IDB Approves 330 Mln Dlrs for Independent Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank approved Wednesday 330 million U.S. dollars in financing for
rehabilitation and expansion of a power plant that will be the
first independent power project in southern Peru.
</P>
<P>
The plant, which will have a generating capacity of 464
megawatts when completed, will provide a reliable source of
electricity to the largest mining region in the country.
</P>
<P>
Most of the installed capacity of the project, to be located in
two sites near the town of Ilo, will serve the electric needs of
the Southern Peru Limited, and the remainder will be sold on the
spot electricity market.
</P>
<P>
The IDB financing consists of a 75 million dollar loan from
ordinary capital and 255 million dollars in syndicated funds.
Tractebel S.A. of Belgium, the parent corporation of Energia del
Sur, is providing some 110 million dollars in financing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
