<DOCNO> XIE19980305.0322 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Imposes Dumping Duties on China Steel Alloy Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) said
Wednesday that it had imposed definitive anti-dumping duties on
imports of ferro-silico-manganese, an alloy used in steel making,
from China.
</P>
<P>
The EU announced its decision in a statement published in its
Official Journal. It also said that it would extend duties on
alloy imports from Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation bloc, which has decided to end duties on such
imports from Brazil, South Africa and Russia, imposed provisional
dumping duties on Chinese imports last September.
</P>
<P>
Beijing argued that its prices were low because companies had
low labor and operational costs and did not have to pay for any
environmental damage.
</P>
<P>
"Dumped imports, by volume, originating in the People's
Republic of China increased from around 12,000 tonnes in 1993 to
75,400 in 1996, an increase of 526 percent," the EU said in the
journal.
</P>
<P>
It also said the market penetration of dumped Chinese imports
rose to 14 percent from 2.4 percent over the same period.
</P>
<P>
A duty of 58.3 ECUs (some 68 U.S. dollars) per tonne had been
calculated on the basis of the injury margin to apply to imports
from China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
